  "prompt": "Is Quora biased against Donald Trump?",
  "response": "Bias on platforms like Quora can be subjective and often depends on individual experiences and perceptions. Users may have varying opinions regarding how different topics, including Donald Trump, are discussed. Factors that might contribute to perceptions of bias include the types of questions being asked, the responses provided, and the moderation practices in place.\n\nSome users may feel that discussions about Donald Trump are unfavorable or that opposing viewpoints are more prominently featured. Others may find that a range of opinions is represented. It's important to recognize that bias can manifest in many forms, including personal bias from users or the way questions are framed and answered.\n\nFor a more nuanced understanding, users can explore a variety of perspectives and note the diversity of opinions expressed on the platform.",
